'''Abiathar Crescas''' ({{IPA-an|aβiaˈtaɾ ˈkɾeskas|lang}}, {{IPA-ca|əβiəˈtaɾ ˈkɾeskəs|lang}}) was a 15th-century [[physician]] and [[astrologer]] from the [[Crown of Aragon]] (now part of [[Spain]]). He was head astrologer to [[John II of Aragon|King John II]] of Aragon, father of [[Ferdinand II of Aragon|King Ferdinand]] of [[Crown of Aragon|Aragon]].
He could remove [[cataracts]] by a surgical procedure known as [[cataract surgery|couching]]. In 1468 he restored the eyesight of King John in two simple operations, who was completely blind before the surgeries.
Crescas was a leader of Aragon's Jewish community.
