{{for|American artist|Karen Green (artist)}} {{Infobox philosopher |region = [[Western philosophy]] |era = [[Contemporary philosophy|21st-century philosophy]] |color = |image = |name = '''Karen Green''' |birth_date = |birth_place = |death_date = |death_place = |school_tradition = | institutions = [[University of Melbourne]] |main_interests = [[political philosophy]], [[philosophy of language]] | thesis_title = | thesis_url = | thesis_year = | doctoral_advisor = | doctoral_students = |notable_ideas = | spouse = | education = | alma_mater = [[University of Sydney]] |influences = [[Michael Dummett]] |awards = [[Australian Academy of the Humanities Fellowship]] |website = }}
'''Karen Green''' is an Australian philosopher and Associate Professor of Philosophy at the [[University of Melbourne]]. She is known for her works on women's intellectual history.<ref>{{cite web |title=Books that Changed Humanity {{!}} A Vindication of the Rights of Woman |url=http://www.anu.edu.au/events/books-that-changed-humanity-a-vindication-of-the-rights-of-woman |website=ANU |accessdate=8 August 2018 |language=en |date=3 October 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=O'Neill |first1=Eileen |title=Review of A History of Women's Political Thought in Europe, 1400–1700 |journal=Notre Dame Philosophical Reviews |date=9 November 2009 |url=https://ndpr.nd.edu/news/a-history-of-women-s-political-thought-in-europe-1400-1700/ |issn=1538-1617}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Gallagher |first1=Megan |title=Review of A History of Women's Political Thought in Europe, 1700-1800 |journal=[[Notre Dame Philosophical Reviews]] |date=31 August 2016 |url=https://ndpr.nd.edu/news/a-history-of-womens-political-thought-in-europe-1700-1800/ |accessdate=8 August 2018 |issn=1538-1617}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Karen Green – Marx & Philosophy Society |url=https://marxandphilosophy.org.uk/reviewer/9217_karen-green/ |website=marxandphilosophy.org.uk}}</ref> Green is the president of the [[Australasian Association of Philosophy]]<ref>{{cite web |title=AAP – President |url=https://aap.org.au/about/President |website=[[Australasian Association of Philosophy]] |accessdate=8 August 2018}}</ref> and a Fellow of the [[Australian Academy of the Humanities]] (elected in 2009).<ref> [https://www.humanities.org.au/fellows/fellows/?find_contact_id=3026&ffc_page=11 Fellows: Karen Green], [[Australian Academy of the Humanities]]. Accessed 2018-08-08.</ref>
